name: Alejandra Martinez
tweet: A group in Dallas called Urban Specialists (@URBNSpecialist) has been doing this work — working to reduce violence in city neighborhoods for over 20 years.   I talked to many of its members for @keranew/ @Report4America. Take a listen:  https://t.co/iNkMg7JxDM

name: Alejandra Martinez
tweet: But, what is that? What are violence interrupters? Groups of ex-gang members (all volunteers btw) trained to prevent gun violence.  They essentially cruise the streets of the toughest neighborhoods to identify & intervene in conflicts before they intensify.

name: Alejandra Martinez
tweet: This would mean partnering with community organizations to establish a “violence interrupters” program in January 2021.

name: Alejandra Martinez
tweet: The proposed Dallas city budget states they will “establish violence interrupters — credible individuals who serve as mentors and conflict resolution experts to curb violence from within their neighborhoods...as part of the City’s Reimagining Public Safety effort.”

name: Alejandra Martinez
tweet: Dallas city leaders are looking for solutions to reduce violence & crime (which is up right now).   “Violence Interrupters” was one recommendation made in January by the Mayor’s Task Force on Safe Communities. via @keranews/ @Report4America [THREAD 🧵]  https://t.co/iNkMg7JxDM
